{"info": {"author": "Chad Smith", "author_email": "grassfedcode@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Topic :: Software Development :: Quality Assurance"], "description": "[![](https://img.shields.io/badge/pypi-0.1.0.1-blue.svg)](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/blackdaemon/) <a href=\"https://github.com/ambv/black\"><img alt=\"Code style: black\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg\"></a>\n\n\nA daemon to automatically run the Uncompromising Code Formatter [`black`](https://github.com/ambv/black) by watching a directory or file for changes.\n\n## Installation\n\n```\npip install blackdaemon\n```\n\n## Use\n```\nblackdaemon <directory or file>\n```\n\n## API\n```\n>> python blackdaemon.py --help\nusage: blackdaemon.py [-h] [--recursive | --non-recursive] [--no-run-on-start]\n                      [-v] [-q]\n                      [path]\n\npositional arguments:\n  path               path of file or directory to watch for changes\n\noptional arguments:\n  -h, --help         show this help message and exit\n  --recursive        recursively watch director for changes (default)\n  --non-recursive\n  --no-run-on-start  run black only when files change, not on startup.\n  -v, --version      print version of blackdaemon and black, then exit\n  -q, --quiet        don't emit non-error messages to stderr. Errors are still\n                     emitted, silence those with 2>/dev/null\n```\n\n## Homepage\n[https://github.com/cs01/blackdaemon](https://github.com/cs01/blackdaemon)\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/cs01/blackdaemon", "keywords": "daemon black automation formatter yapf autopep8 pyfmt gofmt rustfmt", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "blackdaemon", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/blackdaemon/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/blackdaemon/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/cs01/blackdaemon"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/blackdaemon/0.1.0.1/", "requires_dist": ["black", "watchdog (<0.9,>=0.8.3)"], "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "Daemon to automatically run black, the uncompromising code formatter.", "version": "0.1.0.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p><a href=\"https://pypi.python.org/pypi/blackdaemon/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/e39eadf5b91addf2d1c0e631e75dc8e6b36eeb80/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f707970692d302e312e302e312d626c75652e737667\"></a> <a href=\"https://github.com/ambv/black\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Code style: black\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/fbfdc7754183ecf079bc71ddeabaf88f6cbc5c00/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f636f64652532307374796c652d626c61636b2d3030303030302e737667\"></a></p>\n<p>A daemon to automatically run the Uncompromising Code Formatter <a href=\"https://github.com/ambv/black\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>black</code></a> by watching a directory or file for changes.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre><code>pip install blackdaemon\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Use</h2>\n<pre><code>blackdaemon &lt;directory or file&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<h2>API</h2>\n<pre><code>&gt;&gt; python blackdaemon.py --help\nusage: blackdaemon.py [-h] [--recursive | --non-recursive] [--no-run-on-start]\n                      [-v] [-q]\n                      [path]\n\npositional arguments:\n  path               path of file or directory to watch for changes\n\noptional arguments:\n  -h, --help         show this help message and exit\n  --recursive        recursively watch director for changes (default)\n  --non-recursive\n  --no-run-on-start  run black only when files change, not on startup.\n  -v, --version      print version of blackdaemon and black, then exit\n  -q, --quiet        don't emit non-error messages to stderr. Errors are still\n                     emitted, silence those with 2&gt;/dev/null\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Homepage</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/cs01/blackdaemon\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/cs01/blackdaemon</a></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 3854614, "releases": {"0.1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e920a49f2834439e3d60dcbbf5c57dbf", "sha256": "f2b3da98a16705416a74ea117cd7f4e060a26eb11455aa32371f54f05d91b543"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "blackdaemon-0.1.0.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e920a49f2834439e3d60dcbbf5c57dbf", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py2.py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 2205, "upload_time": "2018-05-11T16:19:24", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-05-11T16:19:24.700343Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/a1/f2/7cdd1f37079c6260f928ac9823ba546782c6e391949a3f1d5c8d9a804681/blackdaemon-0.1.0.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "8a98aed12e241f5025321cf8fb74a9fb", "sha256": "335dbfa8c63ce15442e2d35cd103b765759cc81ca21c15207df76c8be0966a97"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "blackdaemon-0.1.0.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "8a98aed12e241f5025321cf8fb74a9fb", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 2208, "upload_time": "2018-05-11T16:19:25", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2018-05-11T16:19:25.911639Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/47/ac/e8c6301d88239c13df80cde425212a40e03991f3613ab0f1d46464025830/blackdaemon-0.1.0.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}]